===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han etym|幎}}
Originally written as {{zh-l|幎}}: {{Han compound|巾|冥|c1=s|c2=p|t1=cloth|ls=psc}}. Xu Shen indicates that the character {{m|zh|幎|tr=-}} meant {{m|zh|幔|t=tent|tr=-|ng=today written as {{zh-l|帷幕|tr=-}}}}.

Later the {{zh-l|*六}} was corrupted to {{zh-l|*大}} and the {{zh-l|*巾}} was written under the character, giving rise to {{zh-l|*幂}}.

{{zh-l|*艹}} was added to form a new {{Han compound|巾|幕|c1=s|c2=p|t1=cloth|ls=psc|nocap=1}}. Alternatively, may also be analyzed as {{Han compound|冖|幕|c1=p|c2=s|t1=cover|t2=cover; tent|ls=ic|ls2=psc|nocap=y}}.

